        <Parent_String>service and utility vehicles [300227818], freewheeled vehicles by form or function [300227810], freewheeled vehicles [300227809], land vehicles by form [300215717], land vehicles [300212968], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand-operated utility vehicles usually fitted with a shallow, open receptacle, a wheel or wheels in front, and two unwheeled supports in back and lifted and pushed using two horizontal shafts extending outward from the rear.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vehículo utilitario accionado manualmente, por lo general equipado con un receptáculo abierto y poco profundo, una rueda o ruedas en la parte delantera, dos soportes sin ruedas en la parte trasera, y que es elevado y empujado utilizando para ello dos ejes horizontales extendidos hacia fuera desde la parte trasera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Met de hand aangedreven voertuig voor het vervoer van lasten. Meestal voorzien van een ondiepe, open bak, eventueel met afneembare zijborden, een wiel of wielen vooraan en twee steunen zonder wielen achteraan, die worden opgetild en voortgeduwd met behulp van twee horizontale stangen die uitsteken aan de achterkant.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handgeführtes Gebrauchsgefährt, üblicherweise ausgestattet mit einer Tragmulde, einem oder zwei Rädern vorne und zwei räderlosen Stützen hinten; es wird angehoben und geschoben, indem man zwei horizontal angebrachte Griffe nutzt, die sich nach hinten außen erstrecken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
